1.
The MAC (Medium Access Control) layer is part of the Data Link Layer (Layer 2) of the OSI model.
Position:
OSI Layer 2 → Data Link Layer → LLC + MAC
Functions:
Controls access to wireless medium (who transmits when)
Frame formatting (802.11 frames)
Error detection (FCS)
Retransmission (ACK mechanism)
Addressing (MAC addresses)
Power management
Security handling (EAPOL, encryption triggers)

Significance: Enables reliable communication over a shared wireless medium.

2.
 802.11 MAC Header Format
Main fields:
Field			Purpose
Frame Control		Type, subtype, flags
Duration		Time medium reserved
Address 1		Receiver
Address 2		Transmitter
Address 3		BSSID / Destination
Address 4		Used in WDS
Sequence Control	Frame ordering
QoS Control		QoS handling
HT Control		High throughput info
Followed by:
Payload (MSDU)
FCS (error detection)


